    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I've been hearing a lot of debate about it lately, but it seems like a lot of people are grouping it into the \"climate change\" argument. From an urban planning perspective, is congestion pricing mostly being seen as a necessary tool for hitting environmental goals, or is it more of a complex economic issue?",
